Author: Nik Samokhvalov <nik@Niks-MacBook-Pro.local>
Date:   Mon Apr 6 02:54:18 2026 -0700

    fix(copy): fix copy_in double-Sync crash and empty-row detection
    
    The copy_in function used query::encode() which sends Bind+Execute+Sync,
    then CopyInReceiver sent another Sync with CopyDone.  Two Syncs produced
    two ReadyForQuery messages; the second arrived with an empty response
    queue in the connection driver, causing 'unexpected message from server'
    and killing the connection.
    
    Fix:
    - Add encode_no_sync() to query.rs (Bind+Execute without Sync)
    - copy_in() uses encode_no_sync so only one Sync is ever sent
    - CopyInReceiver None branch now always sends Sync (error path: server
      rejected before copy mode; success path already covered by Done branch)
    - Remove three spurious batch_execute("") resync workarounds that were
      papering over the protocol violation
    
    Also fix: copy data with a single blank line (COPY x FROM stdin followed
    by just a newline before \.) now correctly sends '\n' to the server
    instead of empty bytes.  The payload trailing-newline check was testing
    the joined string (which is "" for one blank line) instead of whether
    copy_data has any elements at all.
    
    copy2 regression test: 767-line diff → 0 (PASS)

